# BIR4: BIR-4 pulse, adiabatic top-hat excitation pulse,
# B1 insensitive excitation pulse requires relatively high peak power
# M.Garwood and Y.Ke, J.Magn.Reson., vol. 94, p.511 (1991).
%
#       Shape Parameters
#       ----------------
fmf     = tns   (frequency modulation function)
fla     = 90.0r (plane rotation angle)
pwbw    = 20.0  (pulsewidth to bandwidth product)
adb     = 10.0  (adiabaticity on resonance)
st      = 1.0   (default status)
su      = b2    (default phase cycle)
c1      = 0.95  (angular truncation constant, 0 < c1 < 1)
wf      = hta   (window function)
wrap    = 0.25  (wrap-around parameter)
dash    = fla   (dash parameter)
steps   = 500   (default number of steps)


